cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the theoretical analysis of multitask learning and proposes a new training algorithm. It also involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as multitask learning is a subfield of AI and the paper proposes a principled approach for learning task similarity. 

The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) tasks, which are common applications of multitask learning. 

Finally, the paper proposes a new training algorithm for neural networks (cs.NE), which is a subfield of machine learning.
